        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 7:24PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 724 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wadesboro, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Wadesboro, Hamlet, Ellerbe, Dobbins Heights, Lilesville,
Morven, McFarlan, Diggs, and Blewett Falls Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
